spanGrp.span: Recorded by Maïa Ponsonnet in the afternoon of 17th July 2012, in Larrambi-no near Weemol, with Maggie Tukumba, working on Dalabon. Maggie tells how her deceased husband sent us a sign when we came to work in Larrambi-no the week before. Glossed in June 13.
she got off [the car] on the eastern side,
and I got off on the western side.
as we walked around the car
here at the ? we nearly met up
MT had heard a noise when we arrived, and interpreted it as a sign from her deceased husband
this is what I heard, indistinctly.
He was knocking for us, sending us a sign.
As we were coming around here,
we'd come here for a recording session
Ah well, it seems that Maia, they came back
they're going to tell stories in traditional language maybe.
Maybe that's what he was telling us,
when he gave us a fright.
check - making a noise in the bush
Do you think he's happy that we came here?
And then he in turn he gave us a fright.
